<item>
            <title>[LU-19597] TBF: remove duplicate codes</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19597</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18192&quot; title=&quot;TBF: generic combination TBF types with different granularities&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-18192&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-18192&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; added a way to mix different TBF types to generate a custom hash for the generic TBF policy. So TBF generic policy is able to manipulate all the types, this makes old policy callbacks obsolete.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The TBF code can be rework to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Remove old TBF policy callbacks and keep only the generic ones&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Use a single hashtable (remove cfs_hash and keep rhashtable).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Unify the way to handle the LRU (some have it, others don&#8217;t)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
